- Second urn: x red, 9 blue (total x + 9 balls)

The probability of getting two balls of the same color is the sum of:
1. P(both red) + P(both blue)

**Probability of both red:**
$$P(\text{both red}) = \frac{8}{15} \cdot \frac{x}{x+9}$$

**Probability of both blue:**
$$P(\text{both blue}) = \frac{7}{15} \cdot \frac{9}{x+9}$$

**Total probability:**
$$P(\text{same color}) = \frac{8}{15} \cdot \frac{x}{x+9} + \frac{7}{15} \cdot \frac{9}{x+9} = \frac{151}{300}$$

Simplifying the left side:
