$P(X > 8) = 0.121060821 + 0.028247525 = 0.149308346$

**For the maximum of three drugs:**
Since the three drugs are independent:
- P(max ≤ 8) = P(all three drugs have ≤ 8 successes)
- P(max ≤ 8) = [1 - P(X > 8)]³
- P(max ≤ 8) = [1 - 0.149308346]³
- P(max ≤ 8) = [0.850691654]³
- P(max ≤ 8) = 0.614941649...

**Therefore:**
P(max > 8) = 1 - P(max ≤ 8)
P(max > 8) = 1 - 0.614941649
P(max > 8) = 0.385058351

